timeline
    title Resources That Became Architectural Constraints
    section 1980s–90s
        Memory : Manual allocation
               : Garbage collection emerges
               : Careless use becomes survivable
    section Late 1990s
        Network Bandwidth : Chatty protocols hurt
                          : Compression and batching
                          : Microservices reintroduce the lesson
    section 2000s
        Database Queries : Query plans matter
                         : Logical correctness ≠ operational fitness
                         : Indexes and explain plans become standard
    section 2010s
        Cloud Spend : Pay-per-use makes waste visible
                    : FinOps emerges
                    : Architecture and bill are coupled
    section 2026
        Tokens : Usage-based billing arrives
               : Prompt design becomes workload engineering
               : Token efficiency becomes architecture
